message.content:
1. TEAEs occurred in ≥ 5% of participants.
2. Some TEAEs were reported at two or more times the rate of placebo.
3. Decreased appetite was a TEAE reported in the forced-dose study.
4. Decreased weight was a TEAE reported in the forced-dose study.
5. Insomnia was a TEAE reported in the forced-dose study.
6. Initial insomnia was a TEAE reported in the forced-dose study.
7. Dry mouth was a TEAE reported in the forced-dose study.
8. Nasopharyngitis was a TEAE reported in the forced-dose study.
9. Irritability was a TEAE reported in the forced-dose study.
10. Dizziness was a TEAE reported in the forced-dose study.
11. Increased heart rate was a TEAE reported in the forced-dose study.
12. Decreased appetite was a TEAE reported in the flexible-dose study.
13. Decreased weight was a TEAE reported in the flexible-dose study.
14. Insomnia was a TEAE reported in the flexible-dose study.
15. Dizziness was a TEAE reported in the flexible-dose study.
16. Dry mouth was a TEAE reported in the flexible-dose study.
17. Upper abdominal pain was a TEAE reported in the flexible-dose study.
18. LDX and OROS-MPH were associated with decreased appetite, decreased weight, insomnia, and nasopharyngitis in the forced-dose study.
19. LDX was associated with irritability and dizziness in the forced-dose study.
20. OROS-MPH was associated with increased heart rate in the forced-dose study.
21. LDX and OROS-MPH were associated with decreased appetite, decreased weight, insomnia, and dizziness in the flexible-dose study.
22. LDX was associated with dry mouth and upper abdominal pain in the flexible-dose study.

messages.content:
Statement: TEAEs occurring in ≥ 5% of participants that were also reported at two or more times the rate of placebo were decreased appetite, decreased weight, insomnia, initial insomnia, dry mouth, and nasopharyngitis (LDX and OROS-MPH), irritability and dizziness (LDX only), and increased heart rate (OROS-MPH only) in the forced-dose study and decreased appetite, decreased weight, insomnia, and dizziness (LDX and OROS-MPH) and dry mouth and upper abdominal pain (LDX only) in the flexible-dose study.
